<p />
Long term, the <code>osg-el*</code> targets will map to the build and destination tags for the current series (e.g., 3.1 today, 3.2 next, etc.). The process for updating the targets is in the Implementation section below.
<p />
<h3><a name="osg_build"></a> osg-build </h3>
<p />
The <code>osg-build</code> script already has a <code>--repo</code> option to select the correct destination repository (family). We will add to the list of accepted values and define the semantics a bit differently to support many release series automatically (i.e., without code changes for each new series). Also, for source-code repository builds <code>osg-build</code> will default to the correct setting of the <code>--repo</code> option, based on the directory within the source code repository.
<p />
